Assert Is Gene to Symbol Mapping Data Frame

Assert Is Gene to Symbol Mapping Data Frame

assertIsGene2symbol(x, severity = "stop")

Arguments

x

data.frame containing Ensembl gene-to-symbol mappings. Must be structured as a two column data.frame with "geneID" and "geneName" columns.
severity

How severe should the consequences of the assertion be? Either "stop", "warning", "message", or "none".

Value

Abort on mismatch.

See also

Other Assert Check Functions: assertAllAreNonExisting, assertAreGeneAnnotations, assertAreTranscriptAnnotations, assertFormalAnnotationCol, assertFormalCompress, assertFormalGene2symbol, assertHasRownames, assertIsAHeaderLevel, assertIsANumberOrNULL, assertIsAStringOrNULL, assertIsAnIntegerOrNULL, assertIsCharacterOrNULL, assertIsColorScaleContinuousOrNULL, assertIsColorScaleDiscreteOrNULL, assertIsDataFrameOrNULL, assertIsFillScaleContinuousOrNULL, assertIsFillScaleDiscreteOrNULL, assertIsHexColorFunctionOrNULL, assertIsImplicitInteger, assertIsTx2gene, assert

Examples

gene2symbol <- gene2symbol("Homo sapiens", genomeBuild = "GRCh37")
